<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=362&amp;p=1869#p1869"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[I hate Windows 8!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=362&amp;p=1869#p1869"><![CDATA[
Two of my sons and myself just got new laptops and we are finding Windows 8 to be unacceptably frustrating! I am an electrical engineer and one of my sons had good technical skills. <br /><br />Classic Shell has been a Godsend! Thank you!!! <br /><br />However, I am personally hoping there is a way to address the two most annoying features of Win 8. <br /><br />1) The upper right method of getting to the Search/Share/Start/Devices/Settings Menu. It keeps appearing randomly. When I try to get rid of it I often end up back at the home screen (with all the tiles showing). It is possible to stop this from appearing at all? <br /><br />2) I am also having issues with my pointer taking off (usually vertically up) when I click a button. It may be that my finger or thumb is touching the touchpad with my thumb when I click. I have used Windows from 3.1 on and never had this issue. I have disabled all the weird Lenovo/Synaptics pointer options and cannot make it stop. <br /><br />Thanks to all the Classic Shell developers. I was about to return the computer and get one with Win 7. Sucks that XP is no longer being supported!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=434">johnsal</a> — Sat Mar 09, 2013 11:18 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
